I"`<p>Given the well-documented interaction between perception and mental imagery, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/working-memory-recruits-sensory-areas-for-housing-representations">sensory deprivation</a> might <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/visual-imagery-brightness-modulates-pupil-size">improve</a> AI-informed <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/mental-model-reconstruction-is-like-malicious-face-recognition">reconstruction</a> of mental imagery. This would be due to a marked increase in the signal-to-noise ratio, as the interference of external stimuli is reduced.</p>
